{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"## S3 implemented + verified LIVE on Gerrit rebar.solutions.navateam.com — 2026-06-30 (commit ca05de9d9)\n\nThe `rebar` project's refs/meta/config carries the LLM-Review label + submit requirement + ACL; submitWholeTopic is server-global. Applied via setup-project.sh (after granting Administrators refs/meta/config push on All-Projects, server-side, so the normal admin SSH push path works).\n\n**Live config (verified via REST):**\n- Label `LLM-Review`: function=NoBlock, values -1..+1, copyCondition=changekind:NO_CODE_CHANGE.\n- Submit requirement `LLM-Review`: submittableIf = `label:LLM-Review=MAX AND -has:unresolved`.\n- Submit requirement `Code-Review`: applicability_expression = `is:false` (DISABLED on rebar) — so LLM-Review is the SOLE applicable gate (bot-only submit, no human Code-Review in v1).\n- ACL: label-LLM-Review granted ONLY to Service Users + Administrators.\n- `change.submitWholeTopic = true` in server gerrit.config [change].\n\n**AC verification (subagent-driven, all PASS):**\n- AC1 — submit blocked until LLM-Review=MAX: a change created via refs/for/master is UNSATISFIED/non-submittable; after admin LLM-Review=+1 -> SATISFIED. (The `-has:unresolved` predicate is present in config; the MAX gate conclusively proven.)\n- AC2 — label exclusive: admin (Administrators) can vote; a regular account (1000001 devuser, Registered Users only) vote was REJECTED with `Applying label \"LLM-Review\": 1 is restricted`.\n- AC3 — copyCondition: a commit-message-only amend (NO_CODE_CHANGE) CARRIED the LLM-Review=+1 to the new patchset; a real rebase onto a moved base (reported TRIVIAL_REBASE, parent 9f3d69e->8891672) DROPPED the vote -> re-review required. Exactly the intended NO_CODE_CHANGE-only behavior.\n- AC4 — submitWholeTopic: changes 22 & 23 on topic `rebar-test`; submitting 22 alone was rejected (\"must be submitted with change 23 ... not ready\"); after approving both, a single submit MERGED both atomically.\n- AC5 — single LLM-Review gate: ADR-0013 records the deliberate single-gate stance (Code-Review override making it non-applicable) + planned evolution (epic 1fa8).\n- Bonus: bot-only submit verified — change 24 with ONLY LLM-Review=MAX shows Code-Review=NOT_APPLICABLE, LLM-Review=SATISFIED (sole applicable gate satisfied).\n\n**Code review (subagent):** VERDICT PASS (no blockers; NITs folded: grep -qxF fixed-string, untracked-groups no-op detection via git add -A + diff --cached, accurate header comment, -1-not-a-veto note in ADR, groups file now includes Registered Users via global:Registered-Users).\n\nThe \"only the bot votes\" end-to-end proof completes in S4 (the bot Service-User account is created there); S3's vote was exercised by an admin (Administrators has the grant) and a regular user was proven unable to vote."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782788993207922001,"uuid":"03949ece-ef6e-4c07-9cb2-de66e13ec049"}